This was a Number 1 pick at a bookstore I was in, and I had also seen it advertised as a new release. I was excited to hear about Jane Mannings experiences with the Latter-day Saint people. Though I am not delusional enough to believe that the African-American's of that time were always treated equally, I also cannot see that Emma and Joseph would have ever knowingly hurt a person they cared and loved as they did Jane. From what I have read, Joseph and Emma loved Jane very much. From my studies it seems out of character for either of them to have spoken about or to Jane in a way that was condescending. I suppose I could be wrong. I suppose most of my thoughts regarding this are simply imagined as was this movie. It felt as if a message or agenda was being pushed where there wasn't any fact-based evidence to support that these events occurred. Perhaps I missed the notice of it being more than historical fiction. Either way, it just felt really off right up until the end. I would not watch it again myself. Would not recommend it either.
